news.title: Ireland's central bank says commercial real estate price shock orderly so far
news.para: The regulator said that while commercial real estate prices have dropped by more than 20% since mid-2020 and may have further to fall, the transmission of the price shock to the domestic financial system has been orderly "up to now".

news.title: Swedish property company SBB to buy back $440 million of debt
news.para: SBB has agreed to buy back 417.2 million euros of its debt for 403.8 million euros, SBB said, having previously announced a purchase up to a maximum of 600 million euros.

news.title: NGT issues notice to central, state pollution boards over illegal sand mining in Balia
news.para: ​The green tribunal also directed the Balia district magistrate to file the action taken report on or before the next date of hearing.

news.title: EFC (I) leases 1.40 lakh sq ft of office spaces in Pune and Noida
news.para: EFC (I) hopes to achieve total revenue of about Rs. 400 crore for FY24 and about Rs 1,000 crore for FY25. It reported consolidated revenue of Rs. 155 crore for H1 of FY24, which was about 1.5 times of full year of revenue for FY23.

news.title: Maharashtra government unlikely to withdraw 1% metro cess on property registration
news.para: Several citizens and realtors have requested the government to withdraw the cess to bring down the stamp duty. The state has earned over Rs3,000 crore till October from the Metro cess since it was introduced in February 2019 in Mumbai, Pune, Thane and Nagpur to fund public infrastructure projects.

news.title: Brick kiln owners move HC against Punjab government's order, get temporary relief
news.para: The court has prohibited the closure of brick kilns and stated that no action can be taken against kiln owners who do not use paddy straw-based pellets.

news.title: Odisha: House amends land reforms Bill, owners of sublet land to benefit
news.para: Those who currently possess homestead or agricultural land sublet to them by the owners, and recognized in government records as 'Sikkim' type land, will get record of rights (RoR) or land pattas and become rightful owner of the property after the Odisha Land Reforms (Second Amendment) Bill, 2023 comes into effect.

news.title: Commercial activities in residential units: Ghaziabad civic body warns owners of notices
news.para: According to the complainant, the Allahabad high court, in a 2004 judgment, declared commercial activities in residential houses in Vasundhara illegal.

news.title: Goa town planning department brings 49,000 sq meter of land under settlement zone
news.para: An applicant filed for 46,839 sqm of land at Reis Magos to be corrected and cleared for construction. In the Regional Plan 2021, the land parcel was earmarked as natural cover with the ‘no-development’ slope.

news.title: Structural audit of 30-year-old buildings mandatory: Navi Mumbai civic body
news.para: The civic body has made structural audit mandatory for all such rickety buildings and a report from the competent agencies must be submitted to the concerned department before March 31, 2024.

news.title: Maharashtra: MHADA set to implement GIS-based property mapping from new year
news.para: Sanjeev Jaiswal, Vice President and Chief Executive Officer of MHADA has directed concerned authorities to initiate the implementation of this system from the beginning of the new year.

news.title: Allotted land not available, Rudra Buildwell gets 'zero period' relief
news.para: On November 16, Chief Justice Pritinker Diwaker and Justice Ashutosh Srivastava gave relief to Rudra Buildwell and another company, Silverline Furnishings and Furniture, whose land allotment had been cancelled over dues.

news.title: Delhi: DDA starts registration of 5,000 EWS & LIG flats
news.para: A total of 27,000 EWS and LIG flats have been constructed under Festival Special Housing Scheme 2023, which will be offered in phases on a first-come-first-serve basis.

news.title: Gurugram: 21 floors in two buildings sealed for violating occupation norms
news.para: After obtaining occupation certificates (OC), several people have carried out illegal construction in buildings for which show cause notices and restoration orders are being given by the department, officials said.

news.title: Three entities sell Home First Finance shares for Rs 753 crore
news.para: The company's promoters -- True North Fund V LLP and Aether Mauritius Ltd -- and Orange Clove Investments BV, a Warburg Pincus affiliate, offloaded shares in two tranches each on the BSE.

news.title: DDA advises Signature View Apartments residents to seek HC help in 100% vacation clause
news.para: The RWA challenged the condition citing its inability to get all 336 flat owners to handover their keys at once, and requested the authority to bring down the 100 per cent vacation clause to 75 per cent, in the hope that the rest will follow the suit soon.

news.title: Construction sites, waste burning on Pune civic body's radar
news.para: Pune Municipal Corporation’s (PMC) squads have started inspection of construction sites and sent notices to six, so far, directing them to comply with the norms.

news.title: Country Garden shares jump after China signals fresh support
news.para: One of the biggest players in China's property industry, Country Garden has racked up debts estimated in June at 1.36 trillion yuan ($191 billion).
